Task
The number of integers in the array
Write a function countIntegers that takes an array arr as an argument and returns the number of elements that are integers.
Example:
• function countIntegers ([0, 4.1, 'f', true, 1, false, 'h']) must return 2.
• the countIntegers ([2.5]) function must return 0.
• the countIntegers ([- 2, 1, 1.4]) function must return 2.
• the countIntegers ([true]) function must return 0.

Solution
function countIntegers (arr) {
 let count = 0;
 for (let i = 0; i <arr.length; i ++) {
  if (Number.isInteger (arr [i]))
  count ++;
  }
  return count;
}
